Reasoning: 
1. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper investigates self-triggered consensus networks in the presence of communication failures caused by Denial-of-Service (DoS) attacks. The paper proposes a time-varying control and communication policies to preserve consensus in the network. This topic falls under the scope of systems and control.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with network coordination and communication policies in the presence of DoS attacks. This topic falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper deals with the issue of cyber-security and Denial-of-Service (DoS) attacks. This topic falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with distributed consensus networks and communication policies. This topic falls under the scope of distributed computing.
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a time-varying control and communication policies to preserve consensus in the network. This topic falls under the scope of artificial intelligence.
